# France Recipes

Welcome to the France section. Here you’ll find classic French recipes with rich flavors, elegant presentation, and timeless techniques.

- Coq au Vin – chicken slowly braised in red wine with mushrooms, bacon, and onions.
- Ratatouille – a rustic Provençal vegetable stew made with eggplant, zucchini, peppers, and tomatoes.
- Crème Brûlée – a silky vanilla custard topped with a thin, caramelized sugar crust.
- Beef Bourguignon – tender beef slow-cooked in red wine with carrots, onions, and mushrooms.
- Soupe à l’Oignon (French Onion Soup) – caramelized onions in rich beef broth, topped with toasted bread and melted cheese.
- Quiche Lorraine – a savory custard tart filled with bacon, cheese, and cream in a flaky crust.
- Niçoise Salad – a hearty salad with tuna, olives, tomatoes, green beans, and eggs, dressed with vinaigrette.
- Tarte Tatin – an upside-down caramelized apple tart with buttery pastry.
- Baguette with Camembert – crusty French bread served with soft, creamy Camembert cheese.
- Profiteroles – light choux pastry puffs filled with cream and topped with warm chocolate sauce.
- Croque Monsieur – a classic grilled ham and cheese sandwich baked with béchamel sauce.
- Madeleines – small shell-shaped butter cakes with a delicate lemon flavor.
